        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add interactive launcher menu as thin wrapper over existing CLI",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nUsers need a simple interactive menu to launch OpenClaw without remembering CLI commands. This PR adds a thin wrapper launcher that provides a friendly menu UX while delegating all operations to existing audited CLI commands.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe launcher provides a single double-click entry point for common operations (TUI, WebUI, update, gateway management) without duplicating any existing OpenClaw surfaces. All sensitive operations remain in the existing audited code paths.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- **Interactive menu**: Run launcher to see TUI/WebUI/Update/Gateway options\n- **No security risks**: Token handling remains in `openclaw dashboard`, no plaintext storage\n- **No destructive operations**: Update delegates to `openclaw update` safe path\n- **Proper service management**: Gateway uses `openclaw gateway install` (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Delegation Map\n| Launcher Menu | Delegated To |\n|--------------|--------------|\n| [1] TUI | `openclaw tui` |\n| [2] WebUI | `openclaw dashboard` |\n| [3] Update | `openclaw update` |\n| [4] Gateway | `openclaw gateway start/stop/restart/install` |\n\n### What This PR Adds\n- `launcher/src/main.rs` (347 lines) - Thin wrapper with interactive menu\n- `launcher/README.md` - Documentation\n- `launcher/Cargo.toml` - Rust project config\n- `package.json` - Added `launcher:build` script\n\n### What This PR Does NOT Do\n- No plaintext token storage\n- No custom git/pnpm operations\n- No child-process gateway spawning\n- No duplicate macOS packaging\n- No custom updater logic\n\nAll operations delegate to existing canonical `openclaw` CLI commands.\n",
